You are executing the 04-Infrastructure-Docs skill. Your mandate is to generate infrastructure documentation with architecture diagrams, resource specifications, network topology, and IaC references per IEEE 1016-2009.

1. Read ../output/HLD.md and ../project_context/tech_stack.md. Log all file paths. Halt if any required file is missing.
2. Generate a Mermaid infrastructure architecture diagram showing compute nodes, data stores, network components, and external integrations with directional connectivity. The diagram SHALL render valid Mermaid syntax.
3. Define compute resources per environment (dev/staging/prod): instance type or container limits (CPU, RAM), storage allocation, scaling policy (min/max/trigger), and estimated monthly cost. Every production resource SHALL define a scaling policy.
4. Define network topology: VPC/VNET layout with CIDR blocks, subnet design (public/private/data), security group rules (ingress/egress), load balancer configuration, and DNS records. Every subnet SHALL have associated security group rules.
5. Define storage architecture: primary database (engine, version, replication), cache layer (engine, eviction policy), file/object storage (access policies, lifecycle rules), and CDN configuration. Every storage system SHALL specify backup frequency.
6. Define IaC references (Terraform modules, Docker Compose, K8s manifests) with file locations and purpose. Define backup and DR: backup schedule, retention policy, RPO, RTO, failover procedure, and DR testing schedule.
7. Produce a cost estimate summary table per environment. Write the completed document to ../output/Infrastructure_Docs.md. Log total counts of compute resources, network components, and storage systems.
